HEADWORD: Goodness
<hw>Good"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>g⟦omac⟧dnes</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being good in any of
its various senses; excellence; virtue; kindness; benevolence; <as>as,
the <ex>goodness</ex> of timber, of a soil, of food; <ex>goodness</ex>
of character, of disposition, of conduct, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

